Mission

The Tunza Watoto Foundation currently is supporting Little Angels Children's home.

The home started back July 2002. We started from a humble beginning with 35 children, total orphans, .

At the moment , we have 59 children. The home is for both boys and girls. The children are brought to our home through Court Order.

We have kids from 2 month old to 17 years old. We have children from play group to p,p,1 to junior secondary.

Then from there form four to either University or college. In all these stages in school, primary, secondary, Universities or Colleges they do have to pay fees.

We have charges of Food, electricity bills, Hospital bills, . Now we have 3children in university, 8 in secondary school 2 in colleges and 5 babies left here at home.

The last two fundraisers of $4000 helped to install a bore hole ad the home now has fresh water supply.

The Corporation is organized exclusively for charitable, religious, educational, and scientific purposes, including, for such purposes the making of distributions to organizations that qualify as exempt organizations under section 501(c)(3) of the Internal Revenue Code, or the corresponding section of any future federal tax code. Within the scope of the foregoing purposes and without limiting the generality of the foregoing, the Corporation is organized and will be operated to provide love, care, and opportunities for orphaned and vulnerable children. We are dedicated to lifting their spirits, ensuring their well-being, and offering them a brighter future. Through holistic support, education, and community engagement, we aim to break the cycle of adversity and poverty, enabling every child to thrive and become a beacon of hope in their community.
